  "title": "Alphabet Q1 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-04-29T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q1",
  "location": "Mountain View, CA",
  "url": "https://abc.xyz/investor/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "sundar-pichai",
      "speaker_name": "Sundar Pichai",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Q1 2025 was a strong quarter across all our major businesses. Search continues to benefit from AI Overviews, which now reaches over 1.5 billion users monthly. Google Cloud delivered revenues of $12.3 billion, up 28% year-over-year, and is now clearly on track to exceed $50 billion in annual revenue for 2025. Our Gemini 2.0 models are deployed across Search, Workspace, and Cloud, and we are seeing strong enterprise adoption. We remain confident that AI will be the defining driver of Alphabet's growth over the next decade."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "anat-ashkenazi",
      "speaker_name": "Anat Ashkenazi",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total revenues were $90.2 billion, up 12% year-over-year. Operating income was $30.6 billion, with an operating margin of 34%. YouTube advertising revenue grew 10% to $8.9 billion. We returned $15.4 billion to shareholders through buybacks and dividends. For Q2, we expect Google Cloud revenue growth to remain in the high twenties percentage range."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:36:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Eric Sheridan at Goldman Sachs."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-eric-sheridan",
      "speaker_name": "Eric Sheridan",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:36:20",
      "text": "Sundar, you mentioned AI Overviews at 1.5 billion users. Can you quantify the monetization impact relative to traditional Search and give us a framework for how that scales?"
    }
  ],
